{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Can I ask you to please recall a time"},{"time":3000,"text":"when you really loved something --"},{"time":5000,"text":"a movie, an album, a song or a book --"},{"time":7000,"text":"and you recommended it wholeheartedly"},{"time":10000,"text":"to someone you also really liked,"},{"time":12000,"text":"and you anticipated that reaction, you waited for it,"},{"time":14000,"text":"and it came back, and the person hated it?"},{"time":17000,"text":"So, by way of introduction,"},{"time":19000,"text":"that is the exact same state"},{"time":21000,"text":"in which I spent every working day of the last six years. (Laughter)"},{"time":24000,"text":"I teach high school math."},{"time":26000,"text":"I sell a product to a market"},{"time":29000,"text":"that doesn't want it, but is forced by law to buy it."},{"time":32000,"text":"I mean, it's just a losing proposition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35000,"text":"So there's a useful stereotype about students that I see,"},{"time":38000,"text":"a useful stereotype about you all."},{"time":40000,"text":"I could give you guys"},{"time":42000,"text":"an algebra-two final exam,"},{"time":44000,"text":"and I would expect no higher"},{"time":46000,"text":"than a 25 percent pass rate."},{"time":48000,"text":"And both of these facts say less about you or my students"},{"time":51000,"text":"than they do about what we call math education"},{"time":53000,"text":"in the U.S. today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55000,"text":"To start with, I'd like to break math down into two categories."},{"time":58000,"text":"One is computation; this is the stuff you've forgotten."},{"time":61000,"text":"For example, factoring quadratics with"},{"time":63000,"text":"leading coefficients greater than one."},{"time":65000,"text":"This stuff is also really easy to relearn,"},{"time":67000,"text":"provided you have a really strong grounding"},{"time":69000,"text":"in reasoning. Math reasoning --"},{"time":71000,"text":"we'll call it the application"},{"time":73000,"text":"of math processes to the world around us --"},{"time":75000,"text":"this is hard to teach."},{"time":77000,"text":"This is what we would love students to retain,"},{"time":79000,"text":"even if they don't go into mathematical fields."},{"time":81000,"text":"This is also something that, the way we teach it in the U.S."},{"time":83000,"text":"all but ensures they won't retain it."},{"time":86000,"text":"So, I'd like to talk about why that is,"},{"time":87000,"text":"why that's such a calamity for society, what we can do about it"},{"time":90000,"text":"and, to close with, why this is an amazing time"},{"time":92000,"text":"to be a math teacher."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"So first, five symptoms"},{"time":96000,"text":"that you're doing math reasoning wrong"},{"time":98000,"text":"in your classroom."},{"time":100000,"text":"One is a lack of initiative; your students don't self-start."},{"time":103000,"text":"You finish your lecture block"},{"time":105000,"text":"and immediately you have five hands going up"},{"time":107000,"text":"asking you to re-explain the entire thing at their desks."},{"time":109000,"text":"Students lack perseverance."},{"time":111000,"text":"They lack retention; you find yourself"},{"time":113000,"text":"re-explaining concepts three months later, wholesale."},{"time":115000,"text":"There's an aversion to word problems,"},{"time":117000,"text":"which describes 99 percent of my students."},{"time":119000,"text":"And then the other one percent"},{"time":121000,"text":"is eagerly looking for the formula"},{"time":123000,"text":"to apply in that situation."},{"time":125000,"text":"This is really destructive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127000,"text":"David Milch, creator of \"Deadwood\" and other amazing TV shows,"},{"time":130000,"text":"has a really good description for this."},{"time":133000,"text":"He swore off creating"},{"time":135000,"text":"contemporary drama,"},{"time":137000,"text":"shows set in the present day,"},{"time":139000,"text":"because he saw that when people fill their mind"},{"time":141000,"text":"with four hours a day of, for example, \"Two and a Half Men,\" no disrespect,"},{"time":144000,"text":"it shapes the neural pathways, he said,"},{"time":146000,"text":"in such a way that they expect simple problems."},{"time":149000,"text":"He called it, \"an impatience with irresolution.\""},{"time":152000,"text":"You're impatient with things that don't resolve quickly."},{"time":155000,"text":"You expect sitcom-sized problems that wrap up in 22 minutes,"},{"time":158000,"text":"three commercial breaks and a laugh track."},{"time":161000,"text":"And I'll put it to all of you,"},{"time":164000,"text":"what you already know, that no problem worth solving is that simple."},{"time":167000,"text":"I am very concerned about this"},{"time":169000,"text":"because I'm going to retire in a world that my students will run."},{"time":172000,"text":"I'm doing bad things"},{"time":174000,"text":"to my own future and well-being"},{"time":176000,"text":"when I teach this way."},{"time":178000,"text":"I'm here to tell you that the way our textbooks -- particularly"},{"time":181000,"text":"mass-adopted textbooks -- teach math reasoning"},{"time":184000,"text":"and patient problem solving,"},{"time":186000,"text":"it's functionally equivalent to turning on \"Two and a Half Men\" and calling it a day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":191000,"text":"In all seriousness. Here's an example from a physics textbook."},{"time":194000,"text":"It applies equally to math."},{"time":196000,"text":"Notice, first of all here,"},{"time":198000,"text":"that you have exactly three pieces of information there,"},{"time":200000,"text":"each of which will figure into a formula"},{"time":202000,"text":"somewhere, eventually,"},{"time":204000,"text":"which the student will then compute."},{"time":206000,"text":"I believe in real life."},{"time":208000,"text":"And ask yourself, what problem have you solved, ever,"},{"time":210000,"text":"that was worth solving"},{"time":212000,"text":"where you knew all of the given information in advance;"},{"time":214000,"text":"where you didn't have a surplus of information and you had to filter it out,"},{"time":217000,"text":"or you didn't have sufficient information"},{"time":219000,"text":"and had to go find some."},{"time":221000,"text":"I'm sure we all agree that no problem worth solving is like that."},{"time":224000,"text":"And the textbook, I think, knows how it's hamstringing students"},{"time":227000,"text":"because, watch this, this is the practice problem set."},{"time":230000,"text":"When it comes time to do the actual problem set,"},{"time":232000,"text":"we have problems like this right here"},{"time":234000,"text":"where we're just swapping out numbers and tweaking the context a little bit."},{"time":237000,"text":"And if the student still doesn't recognize the stamp this was molded from,"},{"time":240000,"text":"it helpfully explains to you"},{"time":242000,"text":"what sample problem you can return to to find the formula."},{"time":245000,"text":"You could literally, I mean this,"},{"time":247000,"text":"pass this particular unit without knowing any physics,"},{"time":250000,"text":"just knowing how to decode a textbook. That's a shame."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253000,"text":"So I can diagnose the problem a little more specifically in math."},{"time":256000,"text":"Here's a really cool problem. I like this."},{"time":258000,"text":"It's about defining steepness and slope"},{"time":260000,"text":"using a ski lift."},{"time":262000,"text":"But what you have here is actually four separate layers,"},{"time":264000,"text":"and I'm curious which of you can see the four separate layers"},{"time":267000,"text":"and, particularly, how when they're compressed together"},{"time":270000,"text":"and presented to the student all at once,"},{"time":272000,"text":"how that creates this impatient problem solving."},{"time":275000,"text":"I'll define them here: You have the visual."},{"time":277000,"text":"You also have the mathematical structure,"},{"time":279000,"text":"talking about grids, measurements, labels,"},{"time":281000,"text":"points, axes, that sort of thing."},{"time":283000,"text":"You have substeps, which all lead to what we really want to talk about:"},{"time":286000,"text":"which section is the steepest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288000,"text":"So I hope you can see."},{"time":290000,"text":"I really hope you can see how what we're doing here"},{"time":292000,"text":"is taking a compelling question, a compelling answer,"},{"time":294000,"text":"but we're paving a smooth, straight path"},{"time":296000,"text":"from one to the other"},{"time":298000,"text":"and congratulating our students for how well"},{"time":300000,"text":"they can step over the small cracks in the way."},{"time":302000,"text":"That's all we're doing here."},{"time":304000,"text":"So I want to put to you that if we can separate these in a different way"},{"time":306000,"text":"and build them up with students,"},{"time":308000,"text":"we can have everything we're looking for in terms of patient problem solving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"So right here I start with the visual,"},{"time":313000,"text":"and I immediately ask the question:"},{"time":315000,"text":"Which section is the steepest?"},{"time":317000,"text":"And this starts conversation"},{"time":319000,"text":"because the visual is created in such a way where you can defend two answers."},{"time":322000,"text":"So you get people arguing against each other,"},{"time":324000,"text":"friend versus friend,"},{"time":326000,"text":"in pairs, journaling, whatever."},{"time":328000,"text":"And then eventually we realize"},{"time":330000,"text":"it's getting annoying to talk about"},{"time":332000,"text":"the skier in the lower left-hand side of the screen"},{"time":334000,"text":"or the skier just above the mid line."},{"time":336000,"text":"And we realize how great would it be"},{"time":338000,"text":"if we just had some A, B, C and D labels"},{"time":340000,"text":"to talk about them more easily."},{"time":342000,"text":"And then as we start to define what does steepness mean,"},{"time":345000,"text":"we realize it would be nice to have some measurements"},{"time":347000,"text":"to really narrow it down, specifically what that means."},{"time":350000,"text":"And then and only then,"},{"time":352000,"text":"we throw down that mathematical structure."},{"time":354000,"text":"The math serves the conversation,"},{"time":356000,"text":"the conversation doesn't serve the math."},{"time":358000,"text":"And at that point, I'll put it to you that nine out of 10 classes"},{"time":361000,"text":"are good to go on the whole slope, steepness thing."},{"time":363000,"text":"But if you need to,"},{"time":365000,"text":"your students can then develop those substeps together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367000,"text":"Do you guys see how this, right here, compared to that --"},{"time":370000,"text":"which one creates that patient problem solving, that math reasoning?"},{"time":373000,"text":"It's been obvious in my practice, to me."},{"time":376000,"text":"And I'll yield the floor here for a second to Einstein,"},{"time":378000,"text":"who, I believe, has paid his dues."},{"time":380000,"text":"He talked about the formulation of a problem being so incredibly important,"},{"time":383000,"text":"and yet in my practice, in the U.S. here,"},{"time":385000,"text":"we just give problems to students;"},{"time":387000,"text":"we don't involve them in the formulation of the problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391000,"text":"So 90 percent of what I do"},{"time":393000,"text":"with my five hours of prep time per week"},{"time":395000,"text":"is to take fairly compelling elements"},{"time":398000,"text":"of problems like this from my textbook"},{"time":400000,"text":"and rebuild them in a way that supports math reasoning and patient problem solving."},{"time":403000,"text":"And here's how it works."},{"time":405000,"text":"I like this question. It's about a water tank."},{"time":407000,"text":"The question is: How long will it take you to fill it up?"},{"time":409000,"text":"First things first, we eliminate all the substeps."},{"time":411000,"text":"Students have to develop those,"},{"time":413000,"text":"they have to formulate those."},{"time":415000,"text":"And then notice that all the information written on there is stuff you'll need."},{"time":418000,"text":"None of it's a distractor, so we lose that."},{"time":420000,"text":"Students need to decide, \"All right, well,"},{"time":422000,"text":"does the height matter? Does the side of it matter?"},{"time":424000,"text":"Does the color of the valve matter? What matters here?\""},{"time":427000,"text":"Such an underrepresented question in math curriculum."},{"time":430000,"text":"So now we have a water tank."},{"time":432000,"text":"How long will it take you to fill it up? And that's it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434000,"text":"And because this is the 21st century"},{"time":436000,"text":"and we would love to talk about the real world on its own terms,"},{"time":439000,"text":"not in terms of line art or clip art"},{"time":442000,"text":"that you so often see in textbooks,"},{"time":444000,"text":"we go out and we take a picture of it."},{"time":446000,"text":"So now we have the real deal."},{"time":448000,"text":"How long will it take it to fill it up?"},{"time":450000,"text":"And then even better is we take a video,"},{"time":452000,"text":"a video of someone filling it up."},{"time":455000,"text":"And it's filling up slowly, agonizingly slowly."},{"time":457000,"text":"It's tedious."},{"time":459000,"text":"Students are looking at their watches, rolling their eyes,"},{"time":461000,"text":"and they're all wondering at some point or another,"},{"time":464000,"text":"\"Man, how long is it going to take to fill up?\""},{"time":467000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":472000,"text":"That's how you know you've baited the hook, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":476000,"text":"And that question, off this right here, is really fun for me"},{"time":479000,"text":"because, like the intro,"},{"time":481000,"text":"I teach kids -- because of my inexperience --"},{"time":484000,"text":"I teach the kids that are the most remedial, all right?"},{"time":486000,"text":"And I've got kids who will not join a conversation about math"},{"time":489000,"text":"because someone else has the formula;"},{"time":491000,"text":"someone else knows how to work the formula better than me,"},{"time":494000,"text":"so I won't talk about it."},{"time":496000,"text":"But here, every student is on a level playing field of intuition."},{"time":499000,"text":"Everyone's filled something up with water before,"},{"time":502000,"text":"so I get kids answering the question, \"How long will it take?\""},{"time":505000,"text":"I've got kids who are mathematically and conversationally intimidated"},{"time":508000,"text":"joining the conversation."},{"time":510000,"text":"We put names on the board, attach them to guesses,"},{"time":513000,"text":"and kids have bought in here."},{"time":515000,"text":"And then we follow the process I've described."},{"time":517000,"text":"And the best part here, or one of the better parts"},{"time":519000,"text":"is that we don't get our answer from the answer key"},{"time":521000,"text":"in the back of the teacher's edition."},{"time":523000,"text":"We, instead, just watch the end of the movie."},{"time":526000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":528000,"text":"And that's terrifying,"},{"time":530000,"text":"because the theoretical models that always work out"},{"time":532000,"text":"in the answer key in the back of a teacher's edition,"},{"time":534000,"text":"that's great, but"},{"time":536000,"text":"it's scary to talk about sources of error"},{"time":538000,"text":"when the theoretical does not match up with the practical."},{"time":540000,"text":"But those conversations have been so valuable,"},{"time":542000,"text":"among the most valuable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544000,"text":"So I'm here to report some really fun games"},{"time":546000,"text":"with students who come pre-installed"},{"time":548000,"text":"with these viruses day one of the class."},{"time":550000,"text":"These are the kids who now, one semester in,"},{"time":553000,"text":"I can put something on the board,"},{"time":555000,"text":"totally new, totally foreign,"},{"time":557000,"text":"and they'll have a conversation about it for three or four minutes more"},{"time":559000,"text":"than they would have at the start of the year,"},{"time":561000,"text":"which is just so fun."},{"time":563000,"text":"We're no longer averse to word problems,"},{"time":566000,"text":"because we've redefined what a word problem is."},{"time":569000,"text":"We're no longer intimidated by math,"},{"time":571000,"text":"because we're slowly redefining what math is."},{"time":573000,"text":"This has been a lot of fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575000,"text":"I encourage math teachers I talk to to use multimedia,"},{"time":578000,"text":"because it brings the real world into your classroom"},{"time":580000,"text":"in high resolution and full color;"},{"time":582000,"text":"to encourage student intuition for that level playing field;"},{"time":585000,"text":"to ask the shortest question you possibly can"},{"time":587000,"text":"and let those more specific questions come out in conversation;"},{"time":590000,"text":"to let students build the problem,"},{"time":592000,"text":"because Einstein said so;"},{"time":594000,"text":"and to finally, in total, just be less helpful,"},{"time":597000,"text":"because the textbook is helping you in all the wrong ways:"},{"time":599000,"text":"It's buying you out of your obligation,"},{"time":602000,"text":"for patient problem solving and math reasoning, to be less helpful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605000,"text":"And why this is an amazing time to be a math teacher right now"},{"time":608000,"text":"is because we have the tools to create"},{"time":610000,"text":"this high-quality curriculum in our front pocket."},{"time":612000,"text":"It's ubiquitous and fairly cheap,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and the tools to distribute it"},{"time":616000,"text":"freely under open licenses"},{"time":618000,"text":"has also never been cheaper or more ubiquitous."},{"time":621000,"text":"I put a video series on my blog not so long ago"},{"time":623000,"text":"and it got 6,000 views in two weeks."},{"time":626000,"text":"I get emails still from teachers in countries I've never visited"},{"time":629000,"text":"saying, \"Wow, yeah. We had a good conversation about that."},{"time":632000,"text":"Oh, and by the way, here's how I made your stuff better,\""},{"time":635000,"text":"which, wow."},{"time":637000,"text":"I put this problem on my blog recently:"},{"time":639000,"text":"In a grocery store, which line do you get into,"},{"time":641000,"text":"the one that has one cart and 19 items"},{"time":643000,"text":"or the line with four carts and three, five, two and one items."},{"time":646000,"text":"And the linear modeling involved in that was some good stuff for my classroom,"},{"time":649000,"text":"but it eventually got me on \"Good Morning America\" a few weeks later,"},{"time":652000,"text":"which is just bizarre, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":654000,"text":"And from all of this, I can only conclude"},{"time":656000,"text":"that people, not just students,"},{"time":658000,"text":"are really hungry for this."},{"time":660000,"text":"Math makes sense of the world."},{"time":662000,"text":"Math is the vocabulary"},{"time":664000,"text":"for your own intuition."},{"time":666000,"text":"So I just really encourage you, whatever your stake is in education --"},{"time":669000,"text":"whether you're a student, parent, teacher, policy maker, whatever --"},{"time":672000,"text":"insist on better math curriculum."},{"time":675000,"text":"We need more patient problem solvers. Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}